DataElement.preferredName: Qualitative Evaluation Survival Status Code java.lang.Long
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A type of evaluation that is primarily descriptive and interpretative, and may or may not lend itself to quantification. Mainly concerned with the properties, the state, and the character (i.e., the nature) of phenomena. It implies an emphasis on processes and meanings that are rigorously examined, but not measured in terms of quantity, amount, or frequency. (www.unfpa.org/monitoring/toolkit/glossary.pdf and Nonprofit Good Practice Guide Glossary)_Continuance of life or existence especially under adverse conditions; includes methods and philosophy of survival.:A condition or state at a particular time.:A system, often of numbered categories, for representation of data._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is a long integer (64-bit two's complement).
